race.comment: SHEZA BETTOR GEM (10) has been excellent of late, and she made it two in a row when successful at her latest appearance over 1770m at this track, getting home by a nose. Hard to know where she gets from this slightly awkward draw. Big chance based on recent form. CLASSIC ARC (4) finished runner-up last start, beaten 1.75 metres, in a far better performance at this track over 1770m. Recent efforts are good enough to win a race of this calibre. SPRING DELIGHT (6) is worth including in all combinations with some early luck. Something for the Multiples: ZOLTON (8)
